One minute data logged during measurement and used to compute mean gauge height for the measurement. Left Bank estimate co-efficient was changed to other 0.8 for all transects in post process. Mag Var of 0.883 deg (May 7, 2014) was used for measurement it was changed to 0.735 deg (June 24, 2014) and applied to all transects in post process. GPS data with RTK correction was obtained during the measurement. Bluetooth was used to communicate with the ADCP and direct serial connection was through Panasonic Toughbook  CF31 built in serial port. As there was no moving bed correction reccomended GPS was not used in the final calculation of discharge. Sources:Import
